      <p>Massive herbivores of tropical lands, <a href="ch73s19.html#MonstersAnimals62">elephants</a> are unpredictable creatures but nevertheless are sometimes used as mounts or beasts of burden.</p>
      <p>This entry describes an African <a href="ch73s19.html#MonstersAnimals62">elephant</a>. Indian <a href="ch73s19.html#MonstersAnimals62">elephants</a> are slightly smaller and weaker (Strength 28), but more readily trained (Wisdom 15). These statistics can also represent prehistoric creatures such as mammoths and mastodons.</p>
